  <thing id="stS2Living" name="Living" description="Warforged are constructs with the living construct subtype. A living construct is a created being given sentience and free will through powerful and complex creation enchantments.{br}{br}Warforged are living constructs that combine aspects of both constructs and living creatures, as detailed below.{br}{br}{i}Features:{/i} As a living construct, a warforged has the following features.{br}{br} - A warforged derives its Hit Dice, base attack bonus progression, saving throws, and skill points from the class it selects.{br}{br}{i}Traits:{/i} A warforged possesses the following traits.{br}{br} - Unlike other constructs, a warforged has a Constitution score.{br}{br} - Unlike other constructs, a warforged does not have low-light vision or darkvision.{br}{br} - Unlike other constructs, a warforged is not immune to mind-affecting spells and abilities.{br}{br} - Immunity to poison, sleep effects, paralysis, disease, nausea, fatigue, exhaustion, effects that cause the sickened condition, and energy drain.{br}{br} - A warforged cannot heal damage naturally.{br}{br} - Unlike other constructs, warforged are subject to critical hits, nonlethal damage, stunning, ability damage, ability drain, and death effects or necromancy effects.{br}{br} - As living constructs, warforged can be affected by spells that target living creatures as well as by those that target constructs. Damage dealt to a warforged can be healed by a {i}cure light wounds{/i} spell or a {i}repair light damage{/i} spell, for example, and a warforged is vulnerable to {i}disable construct{/i} and {i}harm{/i}. However, spells from the healing subschool and supernatural abilities that cure hit point damage or ability damage provide only half their normal effect to a warforged." compset="Subtype" uniqueness="unique">
    <usesource source="S2Eberron"/>
    <tag group="NeedType" tag="tpConst"/>
    <bootstrap thing="raS2WarImm"></bootstrap>
    <eval phase="First" priority="510">perform hero.assign[NoTypeAbil.tpConst]</eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="raS2WarImm" name="Warforged Immunity" description="Immunity to poison, sleep effects, paralysis, disease, nausea, fatigue, exhaustion, effects that cause the sickened condition, and energy drain." compset="RaceSpec">
