  <thing id="iS2MithBod" name="Mithral Body" description="The plating used to build a warforged provides a +5, and you are considered to be wearing light armor. You now have a +5 maximum Dexterity bonus to AC, a -2 armor check penalty, and an arcane spell failure chance of 15%.\n\nThis plating is not natural armor and does not stack with other effects that give an armor bonus (other than natural armor). This composite plating occupies the same space on the body as a suit of armor or a robe, and thus a warforged cannot wear armor or magic robes. Warforged can be enchanted just as armor can be. The character must be present for the entire time it takes to enchant him." compset="MagicArmor">
